{# ── DEFINITION — advisory, plainly (sand, read). (H2: Accounting advisory, plainly.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="advisory-definition" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Plainly</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Accounting advisory, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Accounting advisory is the work that turns accurate books into decisions &mdash; understanding and forecasting cash flow, tracking the KPIs that drive the business, building budgets and forecasts, reviewing performance, and setting financial strategy. Where <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly">bookkeeping</a> records what happened, advisory interprets it and tells you what to do next.</p>
      <p>As automation commoditizes routine data entry, this judgment layer is where the value now concentrates. TechBrot delivers advisory through Certified ProAdvisors &mdash; from lighter reporting added to monthly bookkeeping, up to <a href="/accounting/advisory/fractional-cfo/?intent=fractional-cfo">fractional CFO</a> engagements &mdash; always built on books that are already correct. We focus on operational and strategic finance; your CPA files the taxes, and we coordinate cleanly.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── SERVICES — 6-area routing (dc-card hub-card r-3, white). (H2: Five ways we turn books into decisions…) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="advisory-services">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What we deliver</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:30ch;margin-bottom:28px;">Five ways we turn books into decisions &mdash; and a CFO when you need one.</h2>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in services %}
      <article class="dc-card hub-card"><span class="eyebrow">{{ s.area | safe }}</span><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 8px;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p><p class="prose" style="font-size:13px;margin:0 0 12px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);"><strong style="color:var(--color-ink);">Answers:</strong> {{ s.answers | safe }}</p><a class="hub-card__go" href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.name | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a></article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── JUDGMENT — the shift, prose + opquote (sand, read). (H2: Basic bookkeeping is being automated. The judgment isn't.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="advisory-judgment" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The shift</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Basic bookkeeping is being automated. The judgment isn&rsquo;t.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>For a decade the value in accounting was getting the data in &mdash; categorizing, reconciling, closing. Software and AI are now very good at that, and getting better. The commodity line is moving up, and the firms that only do data entry are moving down with it.</p>
      <p>What software can&rsquo;t do is sit across the table and tell you the truth: that the product line you love loses money, that you&rsquo;ll be tight on cash in March, that the second location isn&rsquo;t carrying its rent yet. That requires someone who understands both your numbers and your business &mdash; and is willing to say it plainly. That&rsquo;s advisory, and it&rsquo;s deliberately where TechBrot is built to compete. Accurate books first; judgment on top.</p>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="opquote"><blockquote>{{ judgment.body | safe }}</blockquote></blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── HONEST SCOPE — is / isn't / coordinate (dc-card r-3, white). (H2: What advisory is, isn't, and who we coordinate with.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="advisory-scope">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Honest scope</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:28px;">What advisory is, isn&rsquo;t, and who we coordinate with.</h2>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for b in scope %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ b.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ b.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PAGE REVIEW & STANDARDS — prose + trust-row (sand, read). (H2: Reviewed by the ProAdvisor team.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="advisory-review" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Page review &amp; standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Reviewed by the ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot approaches accounting advisory. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for accuracy on the scope and boundaries of advisory work. Where our approach or scope changes, this page is updated. Advisory is delivered on accurate books and coordinated with your CPA or EA for anything requiring a license.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source">Page last reviewed: May 2026.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── RELATED SERVICES — dc-card hub-card r-2 (white). (H2: Related services.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="advisory-related">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Related services</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
